00:18:31.610 --> 00:18:32.711
General Dunford:
Mr. President, Vice

00:18:32.711 --> 00:18:36.281
President Biden, Secretary
Carter, distinguished guests

00:18:36.281 --> 00:18:39.318
-- thank you once again for
joining us as we pay tribute

00:18:39.318 --> 00:18:42.654
to our Commander-In-Chief
and the Obama family.

00:18:42.654 --> 00:18:44.823
Mr. President, I had the
distinct honor today of

00:18:44.823 --> 00:18:49.127
representing your soldiers,
sailors, airmen, Marines,

00:18:49.127 --> 00:18:50.028
and Coastguardsmen.

00:18:50.028 --> 00:18:52.431
And as you know better than
most, those men and women

00:18:52.431 --> 00:18:53.465
are busy,.

00:18:53.465 --> 00:18:55.868
Thousands are deployed
across the globe.

00:18:55.868 --> 00:18:57.970
They're meeting our alliance
commitments and deterring

00:18:57.970 --> 00:18:59.805
potential adversaries.

00:18:59.805 --> 00:19:02.708
They're taking the fight to
the Islamic State, Al Qaeda,

00:19:02.708 --> 00:19:05.143
and other extremist
organizations.

00:19:05.143 --> 00:19:07.713
They're maintaining freedom
of navigation and they're

00:19:07.713 --> 00:19:11.817
defending us from threats
in space and cyber space.

00:19:11.817 --> 00:19:14.119
Throughout your time in
office, we've often heard

00:19:14.119 --> 00:19:16.622
you express your
appreciation for their

00:19:16.622 --> 00:19:19.191
service and their sacrifice.

00:19:19.191 --> 00:19:21.560
But this afternoon, Mr.
President, I want to

00:19:21.560 --> 00:19:24.763
express our appreciation for
your leadership and honor

00:19:24.763 --> 00:19:27.466
your service as our
Commander-In-Chief for the

00:19:27.466 --> 00:19:29.301
past eight years.

00:19:29.301 --> 00:19:31.370
Mr. President, we've been at
war throughout your tenure,

00:19:31.370 --> 00:19:33.805
that's a period longer
than any other

00:19:33.805 --> 00:19:35.207
American President.

00:19:35.207 --> 00:19:38.577
And throughout those years,
you've always been there for us.

00:19:38.577 --> 00:19:40.312
You were there in a
situation room where I

00:19:40.312 --> 00:19:42.881
personally witnessed your
thoughtful and careful

00:19:42.881 --> 00:19:46.318
deliberations when ordering
our young men and women in

00:19:46.318 --> 00:19:47.619
harm's way.

00:19:47.619 --> 00:19:49.955
You were there visiting
the force wherever it was

00:19:49.955 --> 00:19:52.658
deployed, ensuring that
our men and women had the

00:19:52.658 --> 00:19:56.562
guidance and support
necessary to get the job done.

00:19:56.562 --> 00:19:58.196
You were there in the
holidays meeting with the

00:19:58.196 --> 00:20:00.799
troops and calling them
around the world to simply

00:20:00.799 --> 00:20:02.267
say thanks.

00:20:02.267 --> 00:20:04.269
You were there when our
wounded warriors return home

00:20:04.269 --> 00:20:05.270
to heal.

00:20:05.270 --> 00:20:08.040
Your constant visits to
Walter Reed were without

00:20:08.040 --> 00:20:11.710
fanfare of ceremony, but
always marked with heartfelt

00:20:11.710 --> 00:20:14.846
words, hugs from moms, and
more often than not, a few

00:20:14.846 --> 00:20:18.183
lunges and pushups alongside
those who were trying to

00:20:18.183 --> 00:20:20.018
recover.

00:20:20.018 --> 00:20:22.721
Finally, Mr. President, you
were there at Dover Air

00:20:22.721 --> 00:20:26.291
Force Base to receive the
remains of the fallen and

00:20:26.291 --> 00:20:29.294
you were there to visit
them at Arlington.

00:20:29.294 --> 00:20:31.930
I could go on, but let me
share a few sentiments from

00:20:31.930 --> 00:20:35.334
the men and women that you
have touched as a leader.

00:20:35.334 --> 00:20:37.569
Lieutenant Colonel Will
Phillips sent this message.

00:20:37.569 --> 00:20:40.739
"Mr. President and First Lady, thank you both for your

00:20:40.739 --> 00:20:43.308
tireless dedication to our nation.

00:20:43.308 --> 00:20:45.844
President Obama, you've set
an example for us all as a

00:20:45.844 --> 00:20:49.681
statesman, a father,
and a husband."

00:20:49.681 --> 00:20:52.618
Corporal David Dennis, who's
currently deployed to Iraq

00:20:52.618 --> 00:20:54.419
told me how much he
appreciated your call on

00:20:54.419 --> 00:20:58.190
Christmas Day to say thanks
for his sacrifice and service.

00:20:58.190 --> 00:21:00.459
Sergeant Major Troxell and
I, by coincidence, met with

00:21:00.459 --> 00:21:03.428
him a few hours after your
call and he was still pretty

00:21:03.428 --> 00:21:05.364
pumped up after that call.

00:21:05.364 --> 00:21:07.566
I was a bit disappointed
because after your phone

00:21:07.566 --> 00:21:09.735
call that morning, a visit
from the Chairman of the

00:21:09.735 --> 00:21:12.304
Joint Chiefs and his senior
enlisted leader actually

00:21:12.304 --> 00:21:13.405
didn't carry much weight.

00:21:13.405 --> 00:21:15.273
(laughter)

00:21:15.273 --> 00:21:18.143
Major Matt Lampart made the
following comment about your

00:21:18.143 --> 00:21:21.513
hospital visit, "When I met
the President, I was just

00:21:21.513 --> 00:21:23.682
regaining the
ability to walk.

00:21:23.682 --> 00:21:26.418
I had some days that were
tough and some days of

00:21:26.418 --> 00:21:29.421
doubt, but shaking hands
with President Obama and

00:21:29.421 --> 00:21:31.723
having a conversation with
him was something that will

00:21:31.723 --> 00:21:33.725
stick with me forever.

00:21:33.725 --> 00:21:36.595
Given the responsibilities
that he shoulders, President

00:21:36.595 --> 00:21:39.431
Obama's thoughtfulness and
common touch were

00:21:39.431 --> 00:21:41.333
pretty inspiring."

00:21:41.333 --> 00:21:44.036
Master Sergeant Keith Norris
described what your support

00:21:44.036 --> 00:21:47.706
for educational benefits as
a senator and as a President

00:21:47.706 --> 00:21:51.543
has meant to his family, "If
it wasn't for the Post-911

00:21:51.543 --> 00:21:54.746
GI Bill, my wife and I could
not have afforded to send

00:21:54.746 --> 00:21:56.515
our children to college.

00:21:56.515 --> 00:21:59.017
My oldest son just graduated
and I'm excited that he's on

00:21:59.017 --> 00:22:02.487
track to be commissioned in
the United States Air Force.

00:22:02.487 --> 00:22:04.656
While I wish he was going
in the Army -- you may have

00:22:04.656 --> 00:22:07.059
figured out that he's a
Master Sergeant in the Army

00:22:07.059 --> 00:22:09.127
-- while I wish he was going
in the Army, I'm incredibly

00:22:09.127 --> 00:22:12.964
proud that he'll be the
first military officer in my

00:22:12.964 --> 00:22:14.966
family's history."

00:22:14.966 --> 00:22:16.935
Chief Warrant Officer Nate
Powell commented on the

00:22:16.935 --> 00:22:21.073
impact of your support to
military spouses, "Like most

00:22:21.073 --> 00:22:23.508
public school teachers, my
wife doesn't earn all that

00:22:23.508 --> 00:22:26.478
much, but she loves
being a teacher.

00:22:26.478 --> 00:22:29.514
Because of the Military
Spouses Residency Relief Act

00:22:29.514 --> 00:22:32.884
that President Obama signed
into law, my family saves

00:22:32.884 --> 00:22:36.154
thousands of dollars a year
that we'd otherwise have to

00:22:36.154 --> 00:22:38.990
pay just because she has
chosen to move with me

00:22:38.990 --> 00:22:43.228
across state lines from duty
station to duty station."

00:22:43.228 --> 00:22:45.664
And on the lighter side,
Captain Alex Lowe, who's an

00:22:45.664 --> 00:22:49.568
Air Force Flight Surgeon is
also apparently a big fan.

00:22:49.568 --> 00:22:51.503
He said, "I'm glad to have
started my service under

00:22:51.503 --> 00:22:55.373
such a charismatic and cool
Commander-In-Chief who can

00:22:55.373 --> 00:22:57.509
also play ball and
sing a mean Al Greene."

00:22:57.509 --> 00:22:59.711
(laughter)

00:22:59.711 --> 00:23:01.747
I can't witness
that, Mr. President.

00:23:01.747 --> 00:23:03.915
I've not had the opportunity
to see that in the situation

00:23:03.915 --> 00:23:06.418
room, but I'm going to take
Captain Lowe's -- Captain

00:23:06.418 --> 00:23:08.053
Lowe's word for it.

00:23:08.053 --> 00:23:11.189
Mr. President, on behalf of
Lieutenant Colonel Phillips,

00:23:11.189 --> 00:23:14.793
Corporal Dennis, Major
Lampart, Master Sergeant

00:23:14.793 --> 00:23:17.662
Norris, Chief Warrant
Officer Powell, Doc Lowe,

00:23:17.662 --> 00:23:20.966
and all of our men and women
in uniform, we recognize and

00:23:20.966 --> 00:23:24.236
appreciate your service,
your sacrifice, your

00:23:24.236 --> 00:23:27.606
commitment to the force,
and your leadership.

00:23:27.606 --> 00:23:30.675
Of course, just as military
families serve, so has the

00:23:30.675 --> 00:23:32.010
Obama Family.

00:23:32.010 --> 00:23:35.247
While unable to join us this
afternoon, Mrs. Obama and

00:23:35.247 --> 00:23:38.650
Mrs. Biden's creation of
joining forces has made a

00:23:38.650 --> 00:23:40.085
lasting impact.

00:23:40.085 --> 00:23:43.155
In significantly expanded
veteran job placement and

00:23:43.155 --> 00:23:44.556
educational opportunities.

00:23:44.556 --> 00:23:48.093
The First Lady's legal
advice and tireless advocacy

00:23:48.093 --> 00:23:51.997
has also benefitted military
working spouses making

00:23:51.997 --> 00:23:55.433
careers more transportable
for spouses who move every

00:23:55.433 --> 00:23:56.768
few years.

00:23:56.768 --> 00:23:59.004
In fact, the entire
Obama family has served.

00:23:59.004 --> 00:24:01.807
It'd be impossible to sum up
all their contributions

00:24:01.807 --> 00:24:02.941
this afternoon.

00:24:02.941 --> 00:24:05.977
So, in closing, I'll simply
say, Sasha and Malia, thank

00:24:05.977 --> 00:24:09.214
you for sharing your mom and
dad with us and the nation.

00:24:09.214 --> 00:24:11.583
Mrs. Obama, thank you for
improving the lives of our

00:24:11.583 --> 00:24:14.653
families and veterans and
thanks for representing our

00:24:14.653 --> 00:24:16.955
nation with such class.

